==English==
===Etymology===
Via Old [[French]] from [[Latin]] [[coniunctio|coniūnctiō]] ('joining'), which is derived from the [[past participle]] of [[coniungere]] ('to join').

===Noun===
'''conjunction''' (''[[plural]]:'' [[conjunctions]])

#{{grammar}}: A word used to join other words or phrases together into sentences. The specific conjunction used shows how the two joined parts are related.
# the act of joining or being joined.
#(''[[astronomy]]''): alignment of two [[solar-system]] objects such that they have the same [[longitude]] as seen from earth.

